  "text": "MPK6 was shown to act as an SA-mediated defence regulator during systemic acquired resistance signal transmission and also to play a vital role in regulating programmed cell death. Whether the SA-induced senescence phenotype in detached leaves of WT plants alters in mpk6 mutant is unclear [CITATION_1] . To compare the response of WT and the mpk6 mutant to the senescence stimulon, SA treatment was applied for the times indicated, after which various senescence symptoms were looked for.",
